title: USGS, The latest quakes across the globe: March 29 to Apr 04, 2010, World, Apr 04, 2010
name: USGS, The latest quakes across the globe: March 29 to Apr 04, 2010, World, Apr 04, 2010
description:
The point shapefile is based on the latest quake information released by USGS's Quake Information Center in Colorado. It includes the 7.2 magnitude quake in Baja California. And it struck just at a depth of 10 Km, i.e, just a little over 6 miles depth, similar to Haiti quake of same magnitude.

There are number of after shocks in the Baja-California and Southern California regions with magnitude of 2.5 or more.
